====Etymology====
Problably from an indoeuropean root *GHEU- "gushing, pouring season" :

Ancient Welsh GAEM "winter"
Breton GOAÑV "winter";
Ancient Irish GAM "winter";
Irish GEIMH(readh) "winter";

Latin HIEMS "winter";
Ancient Greek ΧΕΙΜΑ "winter";
sanskrit HIMÁS "winter";
Albanian DIMËR "winter";

English GUSH;
German GIESSEN "pour";

Russian and slavic ZIMA "winter";

Lituanian ŽIEMA "winter";
Latvian ZIEMA "winter";